article.headline: No. 2 Kansas rallies past Marquette 77-68

images.name: Lawson finds it and gets it to go
images.caption: Dedric Lawson gets the rebound and muscles it up for two to give Kansas a 70-58 lead with 4:39 left.

article.story: NEW YORK -- Dedric Lawson had a double-double with 26 points and 12 rebounds to lead No. 2 Kansas to a 77-68 win over Marquette in the second semifinal of the NIT Season Tip-Off on Wednesday night. Marquette (3-1) led by as many as 12 in the first half before taking a 47-38 lead into the break. Then came the Jayhawks 22-0 run. Marquette went 0-of-10 from the field to start second half as Kansas (4-0) retook the lead in commanding fashion. The Golden Eagles finally scored a basket nine minutes into the second half on Joey Hauser's 3-pointer to make it 60-50. His brother, Sam Hauser, led the Golden Eagles with 20 points while Markus Howard had 18 points. The Jayhawks got 16 points from Legerald Vick while Devon Dotson chipped in with 10 points, four assists and three steals. Kansas will face No. 5 Tennessee in the final on Friday night, while Marquette will play Louisville in the consolation game.

videos.headline: Dotson steals, scoops and scores
videos.description: Devon Dotson collects the steal and later gets the ball back, drives down the paint, scoops and scores to put Kansas up 13-6.

videos.headline: Vick nails deep 3
videos.description: Lagerald Vick fakes the pass, spins to make space and hits the deep three to bring the Kansas lead up to 19-11.

videos.headline: Azubuike throws it down
videos.description: Kansas' Udoka Azubuike crushes the rim with nasty alley-oop dunk off a Dedric Lawson pass to cut Marquette's lead to 47-42.

videos.headline: Morrow extends and denies
videos.description: Ed Morrow clears Devon Dotson's shot to give Marquette another possession.

videos.headline: Azubuike destroys the rim
videos.description: Off the pick-and-roll, Udoka Azubuike maneuvers, waits and crushes the rim to cut Marquette's lead to 47-46.

videos.headline: Garrett knocks down 3-pointer to extend Kansas lead
videos.description: Devon Dotson turns on the speed, scoops and scores it high off the glass and later Marcus Garrett nails a deep three to add to a 17-0 run and extend Kansas' lead to 53-47.

videos.headline: Dotson breaks free for Vick fast-break layup
videos.description: Off the Marquette miss, Devon Dotson breaks free with a crossover and finds Lagerald Vick for the easy two.
